flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: Scheduled MRP run completion or a BOM/production schedule change (new BOM release, forecast update, or exception detection).]
  A --> N1[Stream: DDM/Crawlers - Ingest master and transactional data (BOM, production schedule, inventory, open POs)]
  N1 --> N2[Cortex: Cortex Auto Forecast / Safety Stock Service - Compute demand signal and dynamic inventory targets (forecast + safety stock)]
  N2 --> N3{Agent: Agentic AI (Process Builder orchestrating Agent Team + RCA Service) - Assess shortage risk and supplier constraints; generate candidate release plan}
  N3 -->|Primary| N4[PB: Remote Functions + Process Builder (Transaction) - Execute releases: write release schedules to SAP and transmit to suppliers]
  N4 --> N5[PB: CWB Lifecycle / UI Screen - Surface exceptions and recommended overrides for human review]
  N5 --> N6[Agent: Process Builder Notification / Agent Team - Notify suppliers and stakeholders of final releases and exceptions]
  N6 --> Z1[Outcome: Timely supplier releases aligned to production needs with reduced expedited buys and obsolescence, lower COGS through optimized sourcing and lot-sizing, improved OTIF, and reduced working capital via dynamic safety stock and prioritized releases.]
  N3 -->|Supplier capacity required quantity...| B1[Agentic AI attempts alternative actions: split release across multiple suppliers, reschedule deliveries, or propose production sequence adjustments; if no feasible automation, create CWB for planner escalation.]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Minimized production disruption by using alternative suppliers or modified schedules; constrained items routed to human approval when necessary.]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N3 -->|Significant BOM integrity issue detec...| B2[Flag BOM error via Process Builder - create Action Item and pause automated release for affected items; notify engineering and planning owners via CWB Lifecycle.]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Prevents incorrect releases and downstream scrap/expedite; accelerates cross-functional resolution of BOM issues.]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N3 -->|Forecast deviation or demand spike be...| B3[Trigger on-demand re-run of safety stock and release planning (Agentic AI + Cortex); if risk persists, generate prioritized expedite list and financial impact summary for management review.]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Rapid adaptation to demand shocks with prioritized releases and visibility into cost/service tradeoffs.]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]